724986f-a.title: Queens: 6th Avenue - 150th Street
724986f-a.text:
150-74 6th Avenue, south side, between 150th Street, and
Powells Cove Boulevard, Whitestone, showing the new armory of
the Fourth Battalion New York Naval Militia, erected by the Works
Progress Administration. For additional data see The New York
Times, Sept. 27, 1937, page 23, report of Colonel Somervell.
Federal Art Project -- W.P.A.  October, 1936
Photographic Division
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE

724987f-a.title: Queens: 6th Avenue - 150th Street
724987f-a.text:
6th Avenue, between 150th Street and Powells Cove Boule-
vard, Whitestone, showing (left) the Fourth Battalion New York
Naval Militia Armory and the boat house. These are being built
by the Works Progress Administration.
